Hometown hero Siya Kolisi meets with his father and brother before he parades the Webb Ellis Cup through Port Elizabeth with the rest of the victorious Bok squad. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Springboks' Rugby World Cup trophy tour is in Port Elizabeth on Sunday. The Boks have been receiving messages of love and support as they parade around the country. READ: Boks fever hits Eastern Cape This morning the team is in Captain Siya Kolisi's hometown. They will end the tour on Monday in Cape Town.